Top of the line custom window treatments throughout.

description:
Recently sold: $345,000. 3d Matterport tour coming soon. Coming live to the MLS on Thursday September 19th. Please contact listing agents Lyman and Denise Jenkins at 612-418-6044 OR 612-490-2733 OR Teamjenkins@results.net.

Imagine living in convenient southern Blaine while enjoying the serenity of a log cabin in the country and also enjoying lots of modern updates! Now imagine on top of that having a separate heated and finished 24x20 workshop/studio/office space perfect for artists, craftspeople, and all types of home-based business owners. You'll also get lots of storage and a huge garage with new garage doors on over an acre adjacent to wooded privacy at the end of a dead end cul de sac! Sound too good to be true? It?s not...  it?s real...  and you can have it!!

Here it is, folks. Ready for you to purchase your own haven of tranquility. The main level features hardwood and tile floors, a rustic and modern kitchen/dining open floor plan, a stone surround wood burning fireplace, a full bath, a large bedroom, a large living room and two porches. Just off the rear porch is an enormous and freshly painted deck overlooking the awesome backyard. Upstairs you'll find three more huge bedrooms and another bathroom in addition to a large storage closet. In the basement you'll find lots of storage, a workout space, a family/theater room and a cozy lounge for entertaining. No need to worry about the heating and cooling system - the current owners have that handled and its been recently replaced. The windows aren't new but they're not old either, and the log siding has been professionally restored and reconditioned by log home pros from Pennsylvania!! 

This is truly a rare opportunity that you will not want to miss. If you are tired of the cookie cutter suburban homes and want something truly unique without sacrificing convenience, look no further. Call this place home and love where you live.

description:
Recently sold: $475,000. Another beautiful floorplan brought to your by Simmer Brothers Homes, this 5 bed, 4 bath Woodland Village home holds nothing back! The huge gourmet kitchen is perfect for your next family cook-off featuring a massive double wide fridge & freezer! 
4 bedrooms & laundry room located upstairs complete with master suite! Downstairs welcomes you with a brand new theater room perfect for that next family movie night or College Game Day watch party!

Recently sold: $425,000. Rare opportunity for single level living in Radisson Ponds. This *stunning* executive walk-out rambler has an amazing layout for entertaining & everyday living. Common area features 9' ceilings, hardwood floors&TONS of natural light. Kitchen is thoughtfully laid out with the chef in mind - storage galore, tons of counter space & convenient center island. Deck has been refinished and is GORGEOUS! Main floor master suite w/huge walk-in closet, double vanity, heated floors & soaking tub. Main floor laundry and mudroom. LL walks out to spacious flat yard, well manicured with patio and fire pit. Cozy up in front of the gas fireplace, play games in the amusement area & grab a drink at the wet bar - truly an amazing space! Great storage throughout! And the GARAGE! Heated and insulated, 928 sqft w/lofted storage, workshop area, floor drain & hard to find 9ft doors. Meticulously maintained throughout. Truly a gem of a home! Close to the lakes and amenities, without the the HOA fees and rules!

Laundry room features built in desk area. 2 generous bedrooms round out this great one level home. Master BR w/walk in closet overlooks the nature views, & features master bathroom en suite space w/ high ceilings & separate tub & shower. Don't miss this lovely well taken care of home that you can move right in and enjoy, or decide to make your own. The Lakes of Blaine is a AWESOME master planned community w/ walking & biking paths intertwined with parks, lakes, beaches, sitting areas, & fishing areas. It's truly a one of a kind place to live. Convenient to shopping, restaurants, freeways, hospitals, etc.. PLEASE CALL/TEXT @ 763-439-8314 to set up a private tour prior to this home hitting the MLS.  Email - paulndani@mnrealestateteam.com
Don't miss out, this home WILL sell fast.

description: Recently sold: $580,000. Rare rambler in The Lakes of Blaine awaits its next owner! Custom TJB built home is meticulously cared for and is situated on over a 1/2acre with pond. Gorgeous landscaping makes this property a showstopper with perennials that bloom throughout the seasons. Walk-in to a large great room with newly finished maple floors and large picture windows making you feel like you are living in a tree house! A chef's kitchen with Kitchen Aid stainless appliances, tiered island with granite allows for plenty of seating for socializing and a quick bite to eat. The screened porch with grill deck is the perfect place to unwind. Gorgeous master bedroom and ensuite with newly tiled shower, enameled cabinetry and tiled floors. Second bedroom and full bath on the main which is perfect for guests and/or a growing family. Lower level entertainment space with built-ins, gas fireplace and two large bedrooms. Whole house speaker system you can run from your phone. Don't miss this one!

description: Recently sold: $609,500. This two-story is top-notch! Features such as hardwood floors, energy efficient windows, geothermal system, custom built-ins, barn doors, and rustic wood accents can be found throughout. The open main level is great for entertaining and/or everyday - curl up by the fireplace all winter, grab a good book and head into the versatile sunroom for great morning light, or get some work done in the front study. The kitchen shines with stainless steel appliances, granite countertops, contrasting center island, and a dry bar with separate wine fridge. Upstairs, four bedrooms and a large bonus room await. Downstairs, the walkout family room was made with fun in mind - picture game nights, movie marathons, and football parties. An exercise room, the fifth bedroom, and a full bath complete this level. Enjoy the private yard, backing to mature trees and set on a half-acre lot, yet just minutes to a variety of shops and restaurants!

description: Recently sold: $335,000. Enjoy more, worry less & brand NEW mechanicals such as water softener, air exchanger & HVAC system, plus a newer roof can be found in this terrific 2-story in The Lakes! Professionally cleaned & ready for you to call it HOME. Real hickory hardwoods flow past the versatile front sitting room & into the heart of the home. The kitchen, dining & living room feature a corner pantry, breakfast bar seating, & a cozy fireplace with built-ins on either side. The convenient laundry & mudroom features built-in cubbies as you come in from the attached garage. Host football parties this fall in the lower level family room, complete with a theater screen that was made for game day viewing, and then head out to the deck to play catch in the well maintained, fenced-in yard during half time. Upstairs, 3 of the 4 bedrooms await, including the owner's suite with vaulted ceilings, a large walk-in closet & its own full bath. Enjoy the convenient location near the schools, parks & trails around the lakes. 2019-10-13

Recently sold: $189,900. Welcome home to this fantastic two bedroom, two bathroom, two car garage townhome for sale in Blaine! Located in a fantastic area not far from the mary Elizabeth Park w/easy freeway access for your commute and within the Spring Lake Park School District (ISD 16). The inviting entryway to the home features your own patio space--a great place to grill/relax outdoors! The main level has an open layout w/laminate hardwood floors throughout! The spacious living room includes a large picture window and vaulted ceilings w/skylight that provide tons of natural light! The adjoining dining room leads you into the kitchen w/upgraded granite countertops, tons of storage in the cabinets, cooktop, wall oven and pantry! In addition, the main level has a good sized half bathroom! The upper level of this well maintained townhome for sale in Blaine features a loft space overlooking the living room--great for a family/game room or office! The upper level also has two bedrooms and a full bathroom w/separate tub/shower and a laundry room!

Additional amenities include: two car insulated/attached garage w/asphalt driveway, roof is only 5 years old, AC around 5-8 years old, HOA maintained exterior and so much more! 

Contact Chuck Carstensen with Re/Max Results at 612-290-3809 to setup your showing today!

Recently sold: $358,800. Great 4 level split! Main floor has formal dining room, 4 season porch, and upper level has living room, 3 bedrooms and full bath. Lower level has large bedroom with walk-in closet, full bath, and family room. 4th Level (basement) has laundry and storage area. Wood floors on main level. Windows replaced. 3 Car insulated and heated attached garage & storage shed. New roof 2018. Steel siding. Beautiful corner lot with underground sprinkler system.

description: Recently sold: $330,000. Beautiful and meticulously maintained 4 bedroom, 4 bathroom modified 2-story located in convenient & quiet Blaine neighborhood! This home boasts many updates throughout with open floor plan and tons of natural light. Main level features inviting family room with gas fireplace, vaulted ceilings, huge laundry room, and a spacious eat-in kitchen with newer tile backsplash and appliances, and perfect little desk area. Basement provides large space for potential home theater/game room or another family room, plus a bedroom and bathroom; all with brand new carpet. Enjoy the beautifully landscaped yard on the big deck overlooking flowers, patio, and lush lawn. Newer flooring, paint, light fixtures, windows, AC, furnace & hot water heater; plus roof, siding, sprinkler system and so much more! Assigned to the excellent Anoka-Hennepin school district. Also within walking distance to bus stops for the Spring Lake Park school district, and easy to open enroll.

Recently sold: $241,790. 4 bedroom 2 bath in a 1977 split entry single unit house with attached 2 car garages. Nice kitchen with attached dinning area. large living room with wood fire place and vaulted ceiling. 2 BR and full bath on upper floor. Lower level gets plenty of sunshine, has a family room attached to a wet bar. 2 bedroom and 3/4 bath with shower but no bathtub. the house in located in a quiet neighborhood overlooking a park yet close to shopping areas and retails. School system in Blaine is excellent. The yard has a deck and fire pit.
Damage deposit equal to one month rent. Pets are ok but there is a $500 extra for the damage deposit and $50 extra a month per pet up to 2 small pets or one large pet. 
Tenants are welcome to use all existing  appliances of Fridge, gas stove, dishwasher, microwave, garbage disposal, washer and electric dryer as long as they are in working condition however, landlord is only responsible to continue to provide working fridge and stove/oven.
No section 8. There will be credit and background check that the fee of $40 will be paid by the applicant directly to the company that will provide me with the info.
Blaine, Coon Rapids, Andover, Fridley,  Ham Lake.

tenant pays for gas, electricity, trash, water, sewer. Tenant responsible for all yard work and snow removal. tenants responsible for all alarms batteries.

description:
Recently sold: $549,000. Located in Amen Corner of the TPC  you will find this exceptional single family golf villa located in a neighborhood on the edge of  TPC Twin Cities in Blaine, Minnesota.  Exhibiting a southwest style while capturing the essence of luxury.  Impressive soaring ceilings along with wall-to-wall glass brings together breathtaking panoramic views of the 14th fairway and beyond. The beautiful golf course setting can be enjoyed from an expansive covered deck providing a perfect place for all your outdoor entertaining.

This inviting executive home in Amen Corner is tastefully decorated throughout and meticulously maintained, offering the best in luxury living.   Some of the outstanding features include European kitchen including Cambria countertops, decorative back-splash, a wine and beverage bar, heating floor and raised breakfast bar.  The owners? retreat will take your breath away with its wonderful master bath including oversized tub, a separate shower, heated flooring , furniture quality vanities, custom audio and a spacious walk-in closet. The lower level provides generous 9 foot ceiling, innovative design in cabinetry and lighting, additional bedrooms, a game room, off of a large open family room which includes a 3 sided fireplace and wet-bar with access through double doors to lower level patio including space for hot tub and mounted TV.

This is a perfect place to call home!

description:
Recently sold: $221,000. This place is truly magical. Peaceful. Wake up to a flock of geese launching off the water. 2 Master suite bedrooms both with walk-ins and their own bathroom. Small loft area. Optimal open floor layout. Bedrooms are massive. Master suite has a jacuzzi tub and stand up shower, Massiv walk-in closet and french doors. Gorgeous hardwood floor on main level and granite counter tops. 2 car-garage. Pond directly in front. Maintenance free (this home is in an association).

Short term opportunity for someone in transition who doesn't want to unpack everything! Fully furnished if you prefer. Utilities and internet are baked into the rental cost so you will not need to put any bills in your name for a shorter lease. One payment for everything. Text or email is best for any questions, and I am happy to answer them!
